{"word":"ἅρμα","slug":"ἅρμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἅρμα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>*<a href='S:ἄρω'><el>ἄρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a chariot</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>a war-chariot</i>, with two wheels, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; often in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> for sg., <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>chariot and horses, the yoked chariot</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>: also <i>the team, the horses</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}